Former President of Nigeria, Olusegun Obasanjo, sent his condolence to popular singer, Daniel Oyebanjo, a.k.a Dbanj over the death of his son David Jnr. Dbanj confirmed the death of Daniel, fondly referred to as Daniel the 3rd on Sunday night on his Instagram page. Sharing a black picture, he wrote @iambangalee, “Trying times but my God is always and forever faithful.” Daniel, who celebrated his first birthday in May, reportedly drowned in the family pool. Obasanjo who wrote on his twitter handle @chief_obasanjo said “My heart and prayers are with Dapo and his family. “No parent should ever have to bury a child. As a parent, it’s the worst thing imaginable. “May God give you the fortitude to bear the loss, Dbanj,’’ Obasanjo stated. 